  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT291-kilavi">pāṅkaṟku uraittatu. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">Told to the companion. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT291">
          <l> cuṭupuṉa maruṅkiṟ kalitta vēṉaṟ</l>
          <l> paṭukiḷi kaṭiyuṅ koṭiccikaik kuḷirē</l>
          <l> yicaiyi ṉicaiyā yiṉpā ṇittē</l>
          <l> kiḷiyavaḷ viḷiyeṉa veḻalol lāvē</l>
          <l> yatupulan taḻuta kaṇṇē cāraṟ</l>
          <l> kuṇṭunīrp paiñcuṉaip pūtta kuvaḷai</l>
          <l> vaṇṭupayil pallitaḻ kalaiit</l>
          <l> taṇṭuḷik kēṟṟa malarpōṉ ṟaṉavē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>The drum <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> kuḷir </term> ("kettle drum" according to DEDR 1831) is supposed to be one of the instruments used to drive away the parrots (just as <term xml:lang="ta"> paṟai </term> in KT 193.3, otherwise a "drum"). In any case it clearly seems to be a percussion instrument. </note> in the hand of the creeper woman</l>
          <l rend="indent8">chasing the parakeets falling into</l>
          <l rend="indent"> the millet which has swollen by a field [cleared by] burning – <note place="foot"> Thus Cām., with a clear parallel in KT 198; that would be a better explanation for <term xml:lang="ta"> maruṅkiṉ </term> than a double locative. </note> </l>
          <l>[its] beat, being a sound like music, is pleasant.</l>
          <l>The parakeets just can't rise because of her tone.</l>
          <l>[Her] eyes which are vexed about that [and] cry!</l>
          <l>They have become like <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta">  pōṉṟaṉa </term>: the p.a. presumably is to be understood to be perfective: by crying, the eyes have become similar to the flowers.  </note> blossoms exposed to the cool drops</l>
          <l rend="indent">that disorder the many petals dense with bees</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of the waterlilies that have begun to bloom in fresh mountain</l>
          <l rend="indent6">pools with deep water on the slope.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
